              "name": "broken",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Flash",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "The pilot overcharges the vehicle, causing it to create a brilliant flash of light. All creatures in the bright light from its glow aura must succeed at a DC 19 Fortitude save or be dazzled 1 minute. The firefly's light dims for 10 minutes, reducing its glow to 10 feet of dim light, during which time it can't use flash. Flash stops working if the firefly is broken.",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 100,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "dd40587ebc07c2b386aa95d93fdcc130",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Light",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 458,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Light effects overcome non-magical darkness in the area and can counteract magical darkness. You must usually target darkness magic with your light magic directly to counteract the darkness, but some light spells automatically attempt to counteract darkness.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability_type": "offensive",
          "name": "Glow",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "Powered by magical lightning, this vehicle sheds bright light within 20 feet, and dim light for a further 20 feet.",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 56,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "b767873f1e57f8326b773c8d1e27cc5c",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Electricity",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 455,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Effects with this trait deal electricity damage. A creature with this trait has a connection to magical electricity.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "edition": "legacy",
              "game-id": "01bf3e53d6c0fc7f70419341635bfe8f",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Evocation",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "4.0",
                    "aonid": 1,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "4.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 631",
                    "aonid": 1,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 631",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Core Rulebook",
                  "page": 631,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the evocation school of magic, typically involving energy and elemental forces.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 100,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "dd40587ebc07c2b386aa95d93fdcc130",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Light",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 458,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Light effects overcome non-magical darkness in the area and can counteract magical darkness. You must usually target darkness magic with your light magic directly to counteract the darkness, but some light spells automatically attempt to counteract darkness.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 103,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Magical",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 458,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability_type": "offensive",
          "name": "Hover",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "text": "This vehicle is held aloft by rapidly spinning propellers that enable it to hover 1 foot in the air. It is incapable of flying any higher, and when the pilot stops the magic or the vehicle breaks, it descends 1 foot to the ground.",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
